abstract: A guide to the terms and phrases we’ve heard during the Senate impeachment trial of President Trump.
snippet: A guide to the terms and phrases we’ve heard during the Senate impeachment trial of President Trump.
lead_paragraph: Many big political news events give rise to colorful terms that stick in the public memory. The Teapot Dome. The Saturday night massacre. The stained blue dress. Hanging chads.

abstract: Since losing the 2016 election to Donald Trump, Hillary Clinton has released a memoir about that defeat, launched a political action committee and penned another book about “gutsy women” with her daughter, Chelsea. But Clinton’s most prominent return to the public eye has come at the Sundance Film Festival, where the former Secretary of State unveiled a candid four-hour documentary series, “Hillary.”
snippet: Since losing the 2016 election to Donald Trump, Hillary Clinton has released a memoir about that defeat, launched a political action committee and penned another book about “gutsy women” with her daughter, Chelsea. But Clinton’s most prominent ret...
lead_paragraph: PARK CITY, Utah — Since losing the 2016 election to Donald Trump, Hillary Clinton has released a memoir about that defeat, launched a political action committee and penned another book about “gutsy women” with her daughter, Chelsea. But Clinton’s most prominent return to the public eye has come at the Sundance Film Festival, where the former Secretary of State unveiled a candid four-hour documentary series, “Hillary.”
headline_main: At Sundance, Clinton Warns of Voter Suppression in Election
headline_print_headline: At Sundance, Clinton Warns of Voter Suppression in Election

abstract: Senator Patrick J. Toomey of Pennsylvania indicated to colleagues that he was open to calling witnesses if Republicans could arrange a witness like John R. Bolton and one more friendly to the president.
snippet: Senator Patrick J. Toomey of Pennsylvania indicated to colleagues that he was open to calling witnesses if Republicans could arrange a witness like John R. Bolton and one more friendly to the president.
lead_paragraph: Add another name to the list of Republicans toying with calling witnesses at President Trump’s impeachment trial.

headline_main: Another Republican senator says he’s open to a witness exchange.

abstract: Pam Bondi, one of the president’s lawyers, said the defense team would rather have ignored questions about the former vice president and his son.
snippet: Pam Bondi, one of the president’s lawyers, said the defense team would rather have ignored questions about the former vice president and his son.
lead_paragraph: President Trump’s lawyers began their promised assault on former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. and his son, Hunter, on Monday, describing what they said was significant evidence of corruption that made Mr. Trump’s interest in the case proper.
headline_main: Lawyers begin their assault on Joe Biden and his son Hunter.

abstract: Georgia Rep. Doug Collins, an ardent ally of President Donald Trump and vocal opponent of his impeachment, is expected to announce he will challenge fellow Republican and newly appointed Sen. Kelly Loeffler for her seat this year, a Republican official said Monday.
snippet: Georgia Rep. Doug Collins, an ardent ally of President Donald Trump and vocal opponent of his impeachment, is expected to announce he will challenge fellow Republican and newly appointed Sen. Kelly Loeffler for her seat this year, a Republican off...
lead_paragraph: ATLANTA — Georgia Rep. Doug Collins, an ardent ally of President Donald Trump and vocal opponent of his impeachment, is expected to announce he will challenge fellow Republican and newly appointed Sen. Kelly Loeffler for her seat this year, a Republican official said Monday.
headline_main: Collins Expected to Try Ousting New GA Senator in GOP Battle
headline_print_headline: Collins Expected to Try Ousting New GA Senator in GOP Battle

abstract: TMZ drew a rebuke from a Los Angeles official after going first with the story of the former N.B.A. star’s death. Some other reports turned out to be false.
snippet: TMZ drew a rebuke from a Los Angeles official after going first with the story of the former N.B.A. star’s death. Some other reports turned out to be false.
lead_paragraph: The gossip and celebrity news site TMZ was first with the news that Kobe Bryant had died Sunday in a helicopter crash near Calabasas, Calif. The report was so early, in fact, that many social media users questioned its accuracy.

abstract: Patrick Philbin, a deputy White House counsel, accused the House of following a political schedule, not running a fair investigation.
snippet: Patrick Philbin, a deputy White House counsel, accused the House of following a political schedule, not running a fair investigation.
lead_paragraph: Patrick Philbin, a deputy White House counsel, argued that the House was trying to shove off the hard work of subpoenaing witnesses to the Senate — all because it wanted to impeach President Trump before the election.
headline_main: The House wants the Senate to ‘clean up the mess’ of its unfinished inquiry, lawyer argues.

abstract: The South Carolina woman credited with popularizing a memorable slogan and chant that epitomized the 2008 presidential campaign of then-Sen. Barack Obama has endorsed Tom Steyer's bid for the White House.
snippet: The South Carolina woman credited with popularizing a memorable slogan and chant that epitomized the 2008 presidential campaign of then-Sen. Barack Obama has endorsed Tom Steyer's bid for the White House.
lead_paragraph: COLUMBIA, S.C. — The South Carolina woman credited with popularizing a memorable slogan and chant that epitomized the 2008 presidential campaign of then-Sen. Barack Obama has endorsed Tom Steyer's bid for the White House.
headline_main: Woman Behind 'Fired Up' Obama Campaign Chant Backs Steyer
headline_print_headline: Woman Behind 'Fired Up' Obama Campaign Chant Backs Steyer

abstract: Debates, graphs, writing exercises, art projects and more for teaching and learning about football’s biggest game.
snippet: Debates, graphs, writing exercises, art projects and more for teaching and learning about football’s biggest game.
lead_paragraph: How can you make this week’s Super Bowl relevant to your curriculum? Whether debating football-related controversies, making predictions, analyzing ads, writing descriptions, understanding data and statistics, or learning about head trauma, we have ideas for using The Times and The Learning Network to help you do just that.
